# Example Crontab Configuration for Polkadot Validator Payout Bot
# =================================================================
#
# To edit your crontab:
#   crontab -e
#
# Or for a specific user (e.g., payoutbot):
#   sudo -u payoutbot crontab -e
#
# Crontab format:
# ┌───────────── minute (0 - 59)
# │ ┌───────────── hour (0 - 23)
# │ │ ┌───────────── day of month (1 - 31)
# │ │ │ ┌───────────── month (1 - 12)
# │ │ │ │ ┌───────────── day of week (0 - 6) (Sunday to Saturday)
# │ │ │ │ │
# * * * * * command to execute

# IMPORTANT: Update the path to match your installation directory!
# Replace /home/payoutbot/polkadot-validator-payout-bot with your actual path

# ============================================================
# Option 1: Run every 24 hours
# ============================================================
0 */24 * * * cd /home/payoutbot/polkadot-validator-payout-bot && /usr/bin/node payout.js >> /home/payoutbot/payout.log 2>&1

# ============================================================
# Option 2: Run once daily at 3:45 AM
# ============================================================
# 45 3 * * * cd /home/payoutbot/polkadot-validator-payout-bot && /usr/bin/node payout.js >> /home/payoutbot/payout.log 2>&1

# ============================================================
# Notes:
# ============================================================
# - The script checks the last 7 eras, so running once per day is usually sufficient
# - Eras last approximately 24 hours on Polkadot
# - Rewards can be claimed up to 84 eras after being earned
# - Logs are written to /home/payoutbot/payout.log
# - Email notifications will be sent for each run
# - Use 'crontab -l' to list current cron jobs
# - Use 'crontab -r' to remove all cron jobs (be careful!)
